Steps to Create a Simple React App
1. Install Node.js: Ensure you have Node.js installed. You can download it from Node.js official website.
node -v   # Check Node.js version
npm -v    # Check npm version


2. Set Up a React App: Use create-react-app to set up your project:
npx create-react-app my-react-app
cd my-react-app


3. Start the Development Server: Start the development server to see your app in action.
npm start
This will open your app in the browser at http://localhost:3000.

4. Customize the App: Replace the default content in src/App.js with the following simple code:

import React from "react";

function App() {
  return (
    <div style={{ textAlign: "center", marginTop: "50px" }}>
      <h1>Welcome to My React App!</h1>
      <p>This is a simple React application.</p>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;



5. Add Styling (Optional): Modify src/App.css to style your app. For example:

body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background-color: #f0f0f0;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

h1 {
  color: #333;
}

p {
  color: #555;
}


6. Build for Production: Once you are satisfied with your app, build it for production:
npm run build
This will create a build folder containing static files ready to be deployed.
